SIMPLE: ill-tempered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ill-tempered
<hw>Ill`-tem"pered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
bad temper; grouchy; morose; crabbed; sour; peevish; fretful;
quarrelsome.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> crabbed, crabby, cross, fussy, fussbudgety, grouchy,
grumpy, bad-tempered.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unhealthy; ill-conditioned.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>ill-tempered</qex> I am grown, that I am afraid I shall
catch cold, while all the world is afraid to melt away.</q>
<rj><qau>Pepys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ill-timed</ent>⟦br⟧
